100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 24, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva to address ongoing tensions in Europe, particularly regarding the situation in the Ruhr Valley. In the United States, discussions continued around the effects of Prohibition, with calls for reform growing among various political factions. Meanwhile, the British government faced scrutiny over its handling of labor strikes, as unrest simmered among workers demanding better conditions.
